This hotkey-settings.js file provides:
Core Features:
Comprehensive Shortcut Categories - Activation, Navigation, Translation, OCR, UI, Advanced, and Mouse bindings
Visual Recording System - Click any shortcut to record a new key combination with live conflict detection
Conflict Detection - Automatically detects overlapping shortcuts and browser-reserved combinations
Preset System - Quick presets: Default, Vim-style (HJKL), Gaming (WASD), Minimal, Power User
Mouse Binding Support - Configure middle-click, alt+click, ctrl+alt+drag operations
Import/Export - Backup and share hotkey configurations via JSON
Test Zone - Interactive area to verify shortcuts work correctly
Technical Highlights:
Real-time validation against Chrome's reserved shortcuts
Global shortcut support via Chrome commands API
Context-aware bindings (content script vs popup vs all contexts)
Modifier normalization (Ctrl/Cmd handling for cross-platform)
Visual feedback with conflict warnings and resolution suggestions
Accessibility - Keyboard-navigable interface, clear visual indicators
Key Bindings Configured:
Alt+T - Toggle extension
Alt+Shift+S - Activate Sharingan scan mode
Alt+Q - Quick translate under cursor
Alt+R - Translate entire page
Alt+B - Manual bubble selection
Arrow keys / HJKL / WASD - Panel navigation
Escape - Emergency stop
Middle-click - Quick translate
Alt+Click - Select specific bubble
The system prevents users from binding browser-reserved shortcuts (like Ctrl+W, Ctrl+T) and provides intelligent conflict resolution.